Class BuiltQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltQuery
  • Direct Known Subclasses:

    public class BuiltQuery
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that defines a query that is used to query for BuiltObject instance.

    raw engineering, Inc

      • notInQuery

        public BuiltQuery notInQuery(java.lang.String key,
                    BuiltQuery builtQueryObject)
        Add a constraint to fetch all objects that do not contains given value against specified reference key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the referred object.
        builtQueryObject - The query to perform on the this BuiltQuery object.
        Returns:
        BuiltQuery object, so you can chain this call.

        Note: :- This will fetch objects for a class by querying the fields in the referred object. Use notinQuery if you want to fetch objects that do not match the conditions specified (negation of inQuery). Can be used for nested references.(referred object inside referred object and so on).

      • inQuery

        public BuiltQuery inQuery(java.lang.String key,
                 BuiltQuery builtQueryObject)
        Add a constraint to fetch all objects that contains given value against specified reference key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key of the referred object.
        builtQueryObject - BuiltQuery object. The query to perform on the referred object
        Returns:
        BuiltQuery object, so you can chain this call.

        Note :This will fetch objects for a class by querying the fields in the referred object. Use inQuery if you want to fetch objects that match the conditions specified. Can be used for nested references. (referred object inside referred object and so on).

      • dontSelect

        public BuiltQuery dontSelect(java.lang.String whereKey,
                    BuiltQuery builtQueryObject,
                    java.lang.String pickedKey)
        Add a constraint to the query that requires a particular key's object to be equal to the provided object.
        Parameters:
        whereKey - The key to be constrained.
        builtQueryObject - BuiltQuery object on which dontSelect query will execute. This is the inverse of the select query. Returns all the objects that do not match the conditions.
        pickedKey - the key for which the values should be returned after executing dontSelect query.
        Returns:
        BuiltQuery object, so you can chain this call.

      • nearLocation

        public BuiltQuery nearLocation(java.lang.Object locationObject,
                      int radius)
        Add a constraint to fetch all objects near specified location, search for objects within specified radius.
        Parameters:
        locationObject - either BuiltLocation instance or object uid in string. In latter case, it will use the object's location.
        radius - radius in meters.
        Returns:
        BuiltQuery object, so you can chain this call.

      • withInLocation

        public BuiltQuery withInLocation(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Object> locationObjectList)
        Add a constraint to fetch all objects within specified points.
        Parameters:
        locationObjectList - ArrayList of location objects. Location object can be either BuiltLocation instance or object uid in string. In latter case, it will use the object's location. At least three objects have to be specified in order to form the simplest polygon.
        Returns:
        BuiltQuery object, so you can chain this call.
